    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a preserved example of high-revving analog perfection. Power is derived from the S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring six individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS system for optimized torque across the rev range. The powertrain is mated to a crisp Getrag 6-speed manual and a functional M-variable limited-slip differential. Mechanically, this chassis has been meticulously maintained with documented rod bearing replacement and rear subframe reinforcement, ensuring structural integrity under high lateral G-loads. The suspension remains factory-spec with zero bushing deflection, offering the precise turn-in and telepathic feedback synonymous with the M-division\u2019s golden era. A truly turn-key collector piece for the discerning enthusiast.",
